      • getRegex

        @NotNull
 @Contract(pure=true)
@NotNull java.lang.String getRegex()
        Gets the regex used to determine whether the text should be accepted. An empty String stands for no validation. The default value is an empty String.
        Returns:
        the validator regex or an empty String, if there is none

      • getMaxLength

        @Contract(pure=true)
int getMaxLength()
        Gets the maximum amount of characters the user can have in this text field. The default value is 32.
        Returns:
        the maximum length of the text when it comes to user input

      • setRegex

        @NotNull
@NotNull TextFieldGuiElement setRegex(@NotNull
                                               @NotNull java.lang.String regex)
        Sets the regex used to determine whether the text should be accepted. An empty String stands for no validation. The current text must match this regex.
        Parameters:
        regex - the new regex to use
        Returns:
        the current instance (for chaining)

      • setMaxLength

        @NotNull
@NotNull TextFieldGuiElement setMaxLength(int maxLength)
        Sets the maximum amount of characters the can be in this text field. The current text must not be longer. The value must be positive and at most 250. (The limit protects against malicious clients and helps obey possible client-side limits.)
        Parameters:
        maxLength - the new length limit to use
        Returns:
        the current instance (for chaining)

      • onChanged

        @NotNull
@NotNull TextFieldGuiElement onChanged(@Nullable
                                                @Nullable TextFieldGuiElement.TextChangedAction action)
        Sets the action that should be executed when this GUI element's text is changed by a player. The callback is atomically executed GUI updating wise.
        Parameters:
        action - the action to atomically execute
        Returns:
        the current instance (for chaining)
